As part of efforts to ensure transparency, accountability and value for money on the government execution of educational, health and water projects in their various communities, the Spotlight for Transparency and Accountability a Non-Governmental Organization has organized a town hall meeting in Jajimaji headquarters of Karasuwa Local Government Area and Gashua headquarters of Bade Local Government Area of Yobe State. The community members and other stakeholders including traditional leaders, youth organizations, People Living With Disability, health workers were also enlightened on the federal government Basic Health Care Provision Fund (BHCF), Social Equity Fund, YSCHMA in order to enable proper implementation.In his opening remarks, one of the resource persons, Aliyu Usman Dagona explained some duties of Spotlight For Transparency and Accountability which according to him includes monitoring of all projects to ensure compliance to the contractual agreement as well as proper execution. Dagona added that Spotlight for Transparency and Accountability will not fold its arms to see things done improperly. On his part, the Executive Director of Spotlight For Transparency and Accountability, Mu’azu Alhaji Modu informed that they are determined to ensure proper dissemination of information on the new health programmes in Karasuwa and Bade Local Government Areas and will assess and report back to the government. He solicited for maximum cooperation to enable them to succeed and enable improved livelihood. According to him some of the report reaching them is the attitude of health workers towards patients, lack of qualified enough medical personnel and insufficient water supply and electricity. One of the community leaders from Gasma, Elder Baba Basma Lawan, appealed to the state government to intensify efforts in improving the health system especially the Primary Health Facility in their Gasma community “, there’s a need for fencing, staff quarters and drugs. While Garin Gawo community members in Karasuwa Local Government Area also appealed to Yobe State government appealed for the deployment of health workers to their health facility in order to reduce the maternal mortality rate. Also speaking, the Village Head of Bukarti, Baba Kolo Zanna commended Spotlight for Transparency and Accountability for organizing the town hall meeting which gave them the opportunity to bring out issues affecting their communities.